# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

---

## [Unreleased]

---

## [1.0.0-alpha.3] - 2026-03-17

### Added

- `Result.TryAsync<T>(Func<Task<T>>)` — async counterpart to `Result.Try`, catches exceptions from async delegates
- `IEquatable<Result<T,TError>>` implementation with `Equals`, `GetHashCode`, `==`, `!=`, and `ToString` (`Ok(…)` / `Fail(…)`) in new `Extensions/Result.Equality.cs`
- `.github/workflows/ci.yml` — CI pipeline that runs on every push and pull request to `main` (build + test)
- XML doc comments on all extension files (`Transform`, `Match`, `Recovery`, `SideEffects`, `Inspection`, `Conversion`, `Operators`) and `Static/Result.Try`

### Fixed

- `Match(Action<T>, Action)` void overload: `onFailure` parameter type corrected from `Action` to `Action<TError>` so the error value is always passed to the failure branch

### Improved

- Package now multi-targets `net8.0`, `net9.0`, and `net10.0`
- NuGet package now ships a symbols package (`.snupkg`) for source-stepping in debuggers
- Added `PackageProjectUrl` and `Copyright` metadata to the NuGet package
- Test suite expanded to 150 tests (added `ResultEqualityTests` and `ResultTryAsyncTests`)

---

## [1.0.0-alpha.2] - 2026-03-17

### Fixed

- CI publish pipeline corrected to use GitHub Packages (`https://nuget.pkg.github.com`) with the automatic `GITHUB_TOKEN` instead of NuGet.org, removing the need for a manual `NUGET_API_KEY` secret

---

## [1.0.0-alpha.1] - 2026-03-17

First public pre-release. All core features are implemented and tested. This alpha is intended for early adopters and feedback before the stable 1.0.0 release.

### Added

- `Opale.Tests` — unit test project (xUnit + FluentAssertions) with 131 tests covering 100% of the public API (sync and async)
- `Opale.Samples` — console application with four real-world usage examples:
  - User registration with multi-step validation pipeline
  - CSV file parsing with per-line error collection
  - Async HTTP service calls with `MapError` and parallel fetch
  - Order processing pipeline with payment, `Recover`, and `MapError` to HTTP status codes
- NuGet package metadata (`PackageId`, `Version`, `Authors`, `Description`, `PackageTags`, `PackageLicenseExpression`, `RepositoryUrl`)
- `GenerateDocumentationFile` — XML docs exported with the assembly
- GitHub Actions publish pipeline (`.github/workflows/publish.yml`):
  - Triggered on `v*` tag push
  - Runs full test suite before publishing
  - Builds with the version extracted from the git tag
  - Packs and pushes to NuGet.org
  - Creates a GitHub Release with the `.nupkg` attached and release notes extracted from this file
- Professional `README.md` with full API reference, usage examples, and async section

### Fixed

- `Result<T, TError>.Value` and `.Error` properties were returning `default` instead of the actual stored value. Properties used the C# 13 `field` keyword (auto-generated backing field) while constructors assigned `_value`/`_error` (explicitly declared fields). Fixed by aligning the property getters to use `_value!` and `_error!`

### Improved

- XML doc comments on `Result<T, TError>` updated with accurate `<summary>`, `<typeparam>`, and `<exception>` tags

---

## [0.1.0] - 2026-03-17

### Added

- Core `Result<T, TError>` type with `Ok` and `Fail` factory methods
- Implicit conversion from `T` to `Result<T, TError>.Ok(value)`
- `IsSuccess` and `IsFailure` properties
- `Value` and `Error` accessors with guarded access (throw `InvalidOperationException` on misuse)
- **Pattern Matching** — `Match<TResult>` and void `Match`
- **Transformations** — `Map`, `Bind`, `MapError`, `ToException`
- **Recovery** — `Recover`, `RecoverWith`, `GetValueOrDefault`
- **Side Effects** — `OnSuccess`, `OnFailure`, `Tap`
- **Inspection** — `IsSuccessAnd`, `IsFailureAnd`, `IsContains`
- **Conversion** — `ToOption` (returns `T?`)
- **Exception interop** — `Result.Try(Func<T>)` wraps exceptions as `Result<T, Exception>`
- Full async counterparts for all operations (`*Async` suffix), supporting both sync and async delegates
